  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Upon his arrival in New York, William Lloyd Garrison was taken to George Benson&apos;s residence. Because of the many visitors there, Garrison spent the night at the home of James Sloan Gibbons. There, he met Mrs. Sedgwick, &quot;the famous school teacher of Lenox.&quot; Garrison spent his last evening at James Miller M&apos;Kim&apos;s home in Germantown and saw a large circle of friends.</subfield>
